<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871120-0171 </DOCNO><HL> Hill Samuel Unit Ends Role</HL><DD> 11/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EUROPBOND MARKET NEWS (BON)SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR) </IN><DATELINE> LONDON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hill Samuel Wood Mackenzie (Sterling Debt) Ltd., a unit of merchant bank Hill Samuel Group PLC, said it has withdrawn as a market maker in British government bonds, or gilts.    The bank, which has said it intends to close or sell its debt trading activities, said it didn't find a buyer for the gilt unit. The bank made no immediate comment about its non-gilt debt operations.    Hill Samuel indicated it would shed its securities activities after agreeing to be acquired by TSB Group PLC at the start of this month. </TEXT></DOC>